"title": "5077: Abraham, character of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5077: abraham, character of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Despite some shortcomings as a husband and father, his obedience, faith, hospitality and effective intercession were exemplary. Such qualities led to his being called “friend of God”.</p>\n<h2>Abraham, the friend of God</h2>\n<h3>He was blessed by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:18-Gen14:19\">GEN 14:18–14:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:22\">GEN 21:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:1\">GEN 24:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:35\">GEN 24:35</a></p>\n<h3>He worshipped God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:33\">GEN 21:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:8\">GEN 12:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:4\">GEN 13:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:18\">GEN 13:18</a></p>\n<h3>He had faith in God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:6\">GEN 15:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:18-Rom4:22\">ROM 4:18–4:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:15\">HEB 6:15</a> <em>Abraham's faith is seen in the length of time (25 years) that he waited for the realisation of the promise</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:8-Heb11:12\">HEB 11:8–11:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:17-Heb11:19\">HEB 11:17–11:19</a></p>\n<h3>He was obedient</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:1-Gen22:19\">GEN 22:1–22:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:4\">GEN 12:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:5\">GEN 26:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:20-Jas2:22\">JAS 2:20–2:22</a></p>\n<h3>He was a prophet and intercessor</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:7\">GEN 20:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:16-Gen18:33\">GEN 18:16–18:33</a> <em>As a prophet, God reveals his will to Abraham; as an intercessor, Abraham brings the revelation back to God and pleads for him to change his mind.</em></p>\n<h3>He was called the friend of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:23\">JAS 2:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:6\">GEN 15:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:7\">2CH 20:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:8\">ISA 41:8</a></p>\n<h2>Abraham's weaknesses as head of his household</h2>\n<h3>He was held responsible by God for his family</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:19\">GEN 18:19</a></strong> <em>As the following references show, Abraham did not discharge this responsibility well.</em></p>\n<h3>He exploited his wife in a cowardly way</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:10-Gen12:20\">GEN 12:10–12:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:1-Gen20:18\">GEN 20:1–20:18</a></p>\n<h3>He fathered Ishmael as a result of wavering faith</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:1-Gen16:4\">GEN 16:1–16:4</a></p>\n<h3>He allowed Sarah to mistreat Hagar</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:4-Gen16:6\">GEN 16:4–16:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:9-Gen21:14\">GEN 21:9–21:14</a></p>\n<h2>Abraham's strengths as a member of society</h2>\n<h3>He was well-respected outside his household</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:22\">GEN 21:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen23:6\">GEN 23:6</a></p>\n<h3>He sought to resolve disputes amicably</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:5-Gen13:12\">GEN 13:5–13:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:25-Gen21:31\">GEN 21:25–21:31</a></p>\n<h3>His wealth was a source of prestige</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:35\">GEN 24:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:2\">GEN 13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:1\">GEN 24:1</a></p>\n<h3>He was honoured for his military prowess</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:13-Gen14:21\">GEN 14:13–14:21</a></p>\n<h3>He was concerned to maintain his independence from the Canaanites</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:22-Gen14:24\">GEN 14:22–14:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen23:7-Gen23:16\">GEN 23:7–23:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:1-Gen24:4\">GEN 24:1–24:4</a></p>\n<h3>He showed hospitality to strangers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:1-Gen18:8\">GEN 18:1–18:8</a></strong></p>",
